snippet.title: St. Lawrence College Promos
snippet.description: Hey! St. Lawrence College hit us up to make them some hilarious promos. We had fun. Hope you enjoy them!

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week In Review #156
snippet.description: A heart broken bro's nightmare throws him into a telekinetic alcoholic fit of sun glasses and Wunderpups.

snippet.title: Wonder Pup II: The Rescue
snippet.description: If half of your superhero job consists of you apologizing, or thinking about it, then it may be time to look at alternative ways of helping people.

snippet.title: Me Glasses
snippet.description: The Ice Age was shaped like a pair of kickin' Ray-Bans, directly over North America. Nobody else cared.

snippet.title: Justified Alcoholism
snippet.description:
The support groups were no help at all, since beers just kept popping up around everybody sitting in the circle of trust.

5sf Shirt: http://store.5secondfilms.com/product/5sf-logo-shirt

snippet.title: Sick Nightmare
snippet.description: This is what you get when you spend all night at a rager, telling the coolest stories to all your bros, and you have six tabs of acid duct-taped to your forehead.

snippet.title: The Heart Thief
snippet.description: He tried to write some poetry to cope with the incident, but he couldn't help starting it with "Hey Heart Thief / Why You Always Gotta Be Thiefin' My Hearts?" which was too heavy-handed and melodramatic, even for him.

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week In Review #155
snippet.description: A lost knife gets laid in the future at a sexist golf tournament with old people.

snippet.title: The Last Hole
snippet.description: Most terrifyingly, you can't help but become them. But it's not a gruesome process like The Thing or a bodysnatcher; you just start hating more and more music, oblivious to the ever-growing truth.

snippet.title: Sexism Saves
snippet.description: Stop wives and save lives with this handy-dandy technique! Note: Must have glasses in order to remove them dramatically.

snippet.title: Kelsey From The Future
snippet.description: And lo, the world was saved. The world of FASHION. At least, until she paired her Louboutins with a red purse and just got way too matchy-matchy.

snippet.title: Gettin' Laid
snippet.description: They "know a guy" who can speed up the entire judicial process, book a room for them at a Max Security in the tri-county area, and then get them out by Monday for good behavior. It's wild. It's basically like a bachelor party except you're the hooker.

snippet.title: Hot On The Trail
snippet.description: Retiring from the force because you lost an escaped convict amidst some hanging clotheslines is tough. Going undercover to catch him is tougher. And growing out your facial hair, only to shave it off and fashion a realistic mustache disguise, is toughest of all. Also, getting stabbed in the process is considerably tough.

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week In Review #154
snippet.description: While on the run from the cops a cucumber bandit's ATM transaction leaks vital clues that only Crime Solving Hooker can solve, but first she has to complete her whore-start paperwork.

snippet.title: Start Paperwork
snippet.description: This, coincidentally, was the same answer he gave for "Where Do You See Yourself in 5 Years?" back during the interview process.

snippet.title: Crime Solving Hookers
snippet.description: The "Charlies Angels" reboot went through so many changes from its initial conception, as you can see.

snippet.title: TMI ATM
snippet.description: If you confirm your PIN, it just starts rifling through stuff like your mom's maiden name, your credit card number, what high school you went to, your Everything Password, until finally it just starts revealing porn sites you go to and what videos you prefer there.

snippet.title: Cucumbers
snippet.description: Having non-stop laser eyes really can make those peepers pretty puffy. Thankfully, this time-tested method both rejuvenates AND provides a tasty snack.

snippet.title: Out To Dry
snippet.description: He even switched out his 'hose, because the old one was getting a little sweaty. That's how fast he is.

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week in Review #153
snippet.description: After the divorce, Ben loses the confidence to successfully sniff out dirty diapers in Operating Rooms and charade parties.

snippet.title: Charades
snippet.description: Last time they played Parcheesi, somebody got shot. So that was voted down 3-1 at game night.

snippet.title: Standard Operating Procedure
snippet.description:
Curiously, it gets 4 bars in there and only 1 on the crosstown bridge. O cell phone towers, what wonders ye hold.

Starring the guys from Cyanide & Happiness!

snippet.title: Treating People Like Babies #122
snippet.description: It's hard to see here, but she's actually texting her boyfriend a bunch of silly baby-talk. This guy is just plain crazy.

snippet.title: Confidence
snippet.description: Once science discovered it was mostly peanut M&Ms in there, the money offers dried up and his wife left him. Just to make ends meet, he stooped to answering creepy "Pep Boys cosplay" want ads on Craigslist.

snippet.title: Anniversary Gift
snippet.description:
This year, get her something she'll remember.

Special thanks to Alfonso Faustino, Jr. and David Bush.

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week In Review #152
snippet.description: I know a puppet therapist in Texas who gives terrible advice about shitting in your hands to get a dates. Don't go to him.

snippet.title: Scratches
snippet.description: I know she had a family and everything, yet I just can't help but think, "That's what you get for getting drunk and answering 'Missed Connections' on Craigslist that weren't yours."

snippet.title: Bro Stand-Off
snippet.description:
It was now or never. Everything was on the line. Play it cool and nobody got hurt...or do something really stupid and pay the price. These bros were teetering on the edge of true oblivion. And the worst part of it is, long after it happened, no one could ever figure out Why.

5sf Shirt available here: http://store.5secondfilms.com/

snippet.title: Lady Advice
snippet.description: This isn't anything you couldn't learn in an average issue of Cosmo. At least there, you'd also get to learn 400 spicy ways to please your dead lover.

snippet.title: Everything's Bigger In Texas
snippet.description: It's basically like entering World 4 in Super Mario Bros. 3, except your dignity doesn't get any bigger.

snippet.title: Puppet Therapy
snippet.description: Any great therapist should be able to explain tough concepts, such as psychosexual trauma, schizotypal personality disorders, or the letter "G."

snippet.title: 5SF Presents: Special Edition Re-Release (Week #151)
snippet.description:
Brian Firenzi goes mad with the power of digital technology and redoes all the classics to make them fucking perfect!

Want an AIDS Shirt? Check out our store: http://store.5secondfilms.com/

snippet.title: Late For Work: Special Edition
snippet.description: Our week-long masterclass in digital trickery and filmic enhancery comes to a close with a new take on 5sf's crowning achievement "Late For Work," which absolutely none of us had anything to do with ever.

snippet.title: Absence Of The Towels: Special Edition
snippet.description: With the power of high-definition digital gimcrackery, the controversial becomes uncontroversial in this latest installment of 5-second visioneering. Would you friend this 5sf?

snippet.title: Robodog (Special Edition)
snippet.description: More cinematic revisionist history as we delve into "Robodog," the tale of a boy and his robotic pet that just wasn't quiiiiiiiite all it could've been, according to its filmmaker.

snippet.title: The Brilliant Dr. Eye (Special Edition)
snippet.description:
Our week of Special Edition 5sfs continues as an older, wiser Brian Firenzi turns his attention to a super-old work, "The Brilliant Dr. Eye," and realizes both his true vision for the film as well as the merchandising opportunities within the character.

To buy your very own "Give Him AIDS!" t-shirt check out: http://store.5secondfilms.com/

snippet.title: Death Ray From Space (Special Edition)
snippet.description: World-renowned filmmaker Brian Firenzi delves back into the 5-Second Films archive to revise, rewrite and restore old 5sfs in his original vision. The first in a week-long series, "Death Ray From Space," gives us all a look inside the mind of a put-upon savant whose only constraints are money, time, and lack of digital innovation at the time of filming. With commentary by the filmmaker.

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week in Review #150
snippet.description: After taking too many expired prescriptions drugs a smiling Mormon uses a yo-yo to strangle the tooth fairy who is holding his rock band back.

snippet.title: Flaky
snippet.description: He might have some pretty tasty chops, but it's not worth all the aggravation. There's 11 more where he came from, anyway.

snippet.title: Tooth Fairy
snippet.description: She knew it was on the rocks when he started trying to give her gold-encrusted tooth necklaces. But hanging outside her cloud palace, blasting Peter Gabriel's "In Your Mouth" on a boombox was the last damn straw.

snippet.title: New Trick
snippet.description: To be fair, the yo-yo learns tricks faster, doesn't eat its own poop, doesn't need heartworm pills, AND it gets just as excited when you come home from work. Sympathetic though he may be, the dog is outclassed in every respect.

snippet.title: This Smile
snippet.description: Flip that frown upside down. You'll never know what'll get flipped back at you.

snippet.title: Can Anyone Operate Heavy Machinery
snippet.description: Heroes aren't born. They're medicated.

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week In Review #149
snippet.description: After graduating college a puppet joins a traveling hillbilly jug band and their life story inspires an art film about diarrhea.

snippet.title: Patriarchy
snippet.description: If you don't have at least one fight in your relationship that ends this way, you're doing it wrong.

snippet.title: Roseburger
snippet.description: It may not seem like much these days, but to gain a true appreciation for "Roseburger" you have to look at it in the context of film history to see what boundaries it broke, narrative and technical alike. For example, nothing.

snippet.title: For The Good Of The Band
snippet.description: He saw a flier earlier up the road, right where his car broke down. "Stand-up bassist needed to complete the ultimate hoedown recipe." Sadly, he never knew about the old adage, "Hicks don't truck in metaphors."

snippet.title: Felt
snippet.description: Buster only knows a specific set of words, all of which end in "-ut" sounds. In Buster's world, there really can only be one type of woman, and there can only be one question to ask.

snippet.title: College Is Gonna Be So Sweet
snippet.description: Six words that you can never take back, unlike the 15 pounds you'll gain (note: You won't take back the 15 pounds either, you just have the choice of doing so).

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week In Review #148
snippet.description: An almost psychic foresees sanitation problems for Kelsey's new boyfriend that will cause a riffed in their communication and resourceful sex.
